      "description": "Available now is a collector-grade 2004 BMW M3, a pinnacle of atmospheric engineering. This E46 chassis features the high-revving S54 3.2L straight-six, delivering linear power through six individual throttle bodies and a precision 6-speed Getrag manual transmission. Mechanical provenance is absolute: the double-VANOS system has been fully serviced, rod bearings replaced as preventative maintenance, and the rear subframe reinforced with structural plates. The suspension geometry is sharpened by Bilstein B16 dampers and refreshed polyurethane bushings, ensuring zero deflection under lateral load. Finished in pristine Carbon Black with no oxidation or clear coat failure, this M3 retains its factory limited-slip differential and offers a visceral, analog driving experience that is increasingly rare. A turn-key example for the technical purist.",
